  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-07-21",
    "date": "2020-08-21T18:33:15Z",
    "text": "Badge Transparency Act of 2020\n\nThis bill establishes a framework to require law enforcement officers to visibly display their identification while on duty.\n\nSpecifically, it requires federal law enforcement agencies to enact policies requiring on-duty officers to visibly display identification. State and local law enforcement agencies must implement a substantially similar policy as a condition of receiving funds under the Edward Byrne Memorial Justice Assistance Grant program and the Community Oriented Policing Services program."
  },
